claim.claim-text:
A method for producing porous particles, the porous particles having an average diameter of 0.5 to 50 microns and comprising the assemblages of poorly water-soluble organic compound fine particles for medical use which have an average diameter of 600 nm or less, have a melting point in the range of 80 to 350 degrees C and are crystalline comprising:
(a) mixing a poorly water-soluble organic compound for medical use with a physiologically acceptable salt and a physiologically acceptable polyol;
(b) wet-milling the mixture of (a), wherein the wet-milling is carried out using one apparatus which has no solid pulverization aid made of glass, metal, ceramics or polymer, and wherein the crystal form of the organic compound is maintained;
(c) removing the salt and/or the polyol after the wet-milling and resulting a wet cake;.
(d) mixing water and one or more secondary aggregation preventing agents with the wet cake of the poorly water-soluble organic compound fine particles for medical use obtained by removing the salt and/or the polyol; and
(e) drying on or after spraying a suspension obtained by the mixture of (d).
